:: Carrots {"position":"675,850","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://cdn.theplaylist.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/14204031/Nic-Cage-Vampires-Kiss-750x400.jpg"></img>

You refuse to eat carrots, taking inspiration from Nicolas Cage in the 1988 cinematic masterpiece //Vampire Kiss// to become a creature of the night.

<img src="https://media.tenor.com/PJty5km7PKYAAAAM/eating-panda.gif" style="width:300px"></img>

Unfortunately, you bump into this...raccoon-bear thing? Anyway, he steals your carrot and eats it, making you lose all your credibility as one.


:: Citrus {"position":"950,600","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://external-content.duckduckgo.com/iu/?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.myfooddiary.com%2Fblog%2Fasset%2F2425%2Fbenefits_of_citrus_2x.jpg&f=1&nofb=1&ipt=f9c0f2d5e7baefb3cd628217ffd7ea344112b1f6c9567535628bdad24d664068&ipo=images"></img>

You choose to forego all citrus fruits and live the life of a pirate. 

Unfortunately, like all good pirates, you get scurvy. It’s very embarrassing.

//Click the arrow to the left of the text to return to the last choice.//


:: Continue onto Twitter. {"position":"750,450","size":"100,100"}
You boot up your laptop to investigate this man’s account.

<img src="https://i.redd.it/5se71ob5rcv11.jpg"></img>

As you browse through the thousands of posts, quite a few catch your eye as you think that they are particularly bad advice...

[[Let's detect some baloney!]]


:: Download TikTok. {"position":"925,1350","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://i.etsystatic.com/23039547/r/il/ea1e8c/2329918635/il_fullxfull.2329918635_jttf.jpg" style="width:200px"></img>

Having never used TikTok in your life, you are incredibly confused when you open the app for the first time, but you discover Vercingetorix's account pretty easily (//there's no one else on there named after a Gaulic king//), but there is one account in particular that gives you such a fright you accidentally drop your handy plate of spinach on the floor.

* "Rickets is a serious bone condition caused by a lack of Vitamin D. Rickets is normally acquired in childhood. It results in extremely brittle bones. How do you prevent rickets? [[EGGS!]]" //(He proceeds to drink shot glasses of egg yolk)//

* "Korsakoff syndrome is a disorder of the nervous system, resulting in such symptoms as amnesia, memory loss and apathy. It is caused by a lack of protein, and you can treat this syndrome with...[[MANGOES]]!" //
(He proceeds to slice a mango and eat it)//

* "Scurvy. Our old enemy. Also known as Moeller's disease, this was common among sailors in the 18th century. It's caused by a lack of Vitamin C and results in tiredness and abnormal bleeding. You can avoid scurvy by //(He opens his fridge to reveal a variety of [[citrus fruits]])// eating that good citrussy."


:: EGGS! {"position":"925,1475","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://external-content.duckduckgo.com/iu/?u=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia1.tenor.com%2Fimages%2Fc7037437f1e25d68ac42536cacd5aef7%2Ftenor.gif%3Fitemid%3D7297657&f=1&nofb=1&ipt=3e63b66e319a9e7b622c6e91e6b1710b41f3ca0f528349e453875327af382a38&ipo=images"></img>

While the way Vercingetorix drank eggs is awful and should never be done by any decent human being, all of the information he shared is correct. 


:: Henrion, J. (1870) {"position":"925,1100","size":"100,100"}
Correct! 

<img src="https://images.everydayhealth.com/images/diet-nutrition/all-about-bananas-nutrition-facts-health-benefits-recipes-and-more-rm-722x406.jpg"></img>

While the Banana Quickstep is one of the greatest accomplishments of humankind, it is not related to nutrition and is in fact a dance move and song. 

<img src="https://i.ytimg.com/vi/faDKaHlMaMA/maxresdefault.jpg"></img>

Content you compile your evidence and send it to Ambiorix, confident you have saved him from Vercingetorix's machinations.

[[Text Ambiorix.]]


:: Let's detect some baloney! {"position":"875,450","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ChessPiece21/Baloney-Detectives/main/img/profile.png" style="width:300px"></img>
Looking at Vercingetorix's Twitter, you see several posts that concern you. You don't know how Ambiorix became a fan!

But among all this malarkey, one tweet stands out in particular...

//Click on the [[blue]] word that you think is the fake tweet!//

* "[[Citrus]] fruits are good for you! They prevent scurvy!"

* "If you don't [[drink water]], you will die!"

* "All you need to live forever is [[raw meat]]. Take it from me, I've lived for 2,000 years on a meat-only diet!"


:: MANGOES {"position":"1050,1475","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://comprendre.media/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Mangues.jpg"></img>

Correct! While mangoes are among the greatest fruits of all time, they are NOT a source of protein.

You send this post to Ambiorix. He realizes that this is a "no bueno," leading him to immediately burn all his framed photos of Vercingetorix and vow to be more vigilant in the future. 

<h1>''Congratulations! You detected all the baloney!''</h1>

[[Read the credits.]]


:: Oranges {"position":"925,850","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://images.tripshock.com/activity/3434/Pirate-Ship-Adventure-at-John-s-Pass.jpg"></img>

Arrrrgh, the call of the sea has claimed you, and you find yourself drawn to the life of a pirate. 

In order to sail the 7 seas, you abandon the wretched citrus. 

<img src="https://media0.giphy.com/media/3o7TKPdUkkbCAVqWk0/giphy.gif"></img>

Unfortunately, you get scurvy and all the other pirates make fun of you.


:: Praagman. (2014) {"position":"800,1100","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://preview.redd.it/1h1b78o7agn71.png?auto=webp&s=ac7288a4561dcc0cc495217d8353377232d55c48"></img>

Unfortunately, while //The European Journal of Nutrition// is incredibly boring, and this meme Vercingetorix included in the book sums the article up in a much better way, it is in fact a credible source. 


