:: Scragg, R. et. al. (2017) {"position":"675,1100","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://i.dietdoctor.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/dairy.png?auto=compress%2Cformat&w=1200&h=600&fit=crop"></img>

Unfortunately, while this source is long and definitely looks complicated, it is credible.

Because you don't know what you can do without cheese, the credibility makes you smile.


:: Soy {"position":"800,850","size":"100,100"}
<img src="https://images.ctfassets.net/cnu0m8re1exe/2BDSpnMz4n2VUCdg1r7SyN/4d137969ccbb379a3b519453a237e4cb/shutterstock_1467898517.jpg"></img>

You successfully noticed the work that does not have any source. This proves your initial concerns were not just your own imagination you satisfactorily grin. 

You get a notification that your friend reposted a tweet of Vercingeotrix's, indicating that he's hosting his bestselling book on SciHub! 

You cannot believe this. No disinformation-spreading villain could pen a best selling book!

[[Wait. Could they?]] 


:: Start {"position":"650,325","size":"100,100"}
Your friend Ambiorix has been talking up a social media health influencer’s account - the infamous ''(text-colour:green)[@Vercingetorix]''. 

<img src="https://github.com/ChessPiece21/Baloney-Detectives/blob/main/img/vercingetorix.png?raw=true"></img>

He boasts a large following of 5.7 million tweeters on a global scale, despite only being around for a few months.

You have heard of Vercingetorix for a while, and have heard some less than flattering accounts of him...

[[Continue onto Twitter.]]


:: Text Ambiorix. {"position":"925,1225","size":"100,100"}
You triumphantly present your concerns to Ambiorix, but when he responds to you, you receive a more concerning message:

<img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ChessPiece21/Baloney-Detectives/main/img/text-chain.png"></img>

You have been avoiding the app for a while, but because you want to be a good friend, you decide to...[[Download TikTok.]]


